\begin_layout Subsubsection
Calculation of seasonal bushfire danger 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The investigation used the FFDI to explore seasonal bushfire danger in Victoria.
 The index is used in Australia by authorities to assess fire behaviour
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Lucas2010"

\end_inset

.
 The FFDI yields daily values of bushfire danger.
 The index computation requires meteorological data reported on individual
 weather stations.
 The average of daily values for each weather station yielded regional values.
 On the other hand, averaging the gridded reanalysis data over Victoria
 yielded regional values.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However, this investigation aimed to analyse bushfire danger with a seasonal
